news.title: Seven years on, SEIAA has not decided on green & parking spaces in Mulund project: NGT
news.para: The tribunal order said, “Thus, the status of EC remains that of “deemed inoperative”. The PP (project proponent) stands restrained from carrying out any further work till the issue is decided by SEIAA in terms of order of this Tribunal.’’

news.title: Kumar Mangalam Birla weighs ACC, Ambuja bid, move may invite regulator scrutiny
news.para: Birla's flagship UltraTech is the leading cement player in the country and any bid will face scrutiny from India's anti-trust watchdog. UltraTech's capacity, combined with that of Ambuja Cement and ACC Ltd, the two listed arms of The Holcim Group in India, will reach dominant market share in some states.

news.title: Noida: Ajnara Daffodil residents hit the street over high upkeep fees, few amenities
news.para: Residents alleged that the sewage treatment plant (STP) did not work in accordance with the rules, the club was in a disarray and the swimming pool barely functional. There is no system for garbage segregation either, they said.

news.title: Domestic private equity funds getting bullish on realty bets again
news.para: Revival in demand for housing driven by a combination of factors including record-low interest rates and pandemic-induced realisation of the need of home ownership is helping attract liquidity from these institutional investors.

news.title: Land fraud cases on the rise in Dehradun, 154 recorded in 2021
news.para: The data was released by Dehradun district police after a major land shark gang active across north India was recently busted, and property worth Rs 153 crore of the kingpin, Narendra Tomar, was attached by Uttarakhand STF.

news.title: Rajasthan: Only 25% of total allocated funds for PMAY-G released by centre in 2021-22
news.para: Due to this, only 9,000 houses were built during the last financial year out of the total target of 3.97 lakh houses, the official added.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Savy Ville De families get 15 days to appeal on eviction notices
news.para: TOI had reported last week that 42 families in the condominium feared being evicted after recently coming to know of a 2020 order allowing a finance company to seize flats that had been mortgaged by the developer, who had defaulted on the loan repayment.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Environmentalist write to state on dubious buildings in CRZ areas
news.para: The vice president of Maharashtra Chamber of Housing Industry (MCHI-Navi Mumbai) Manohar Shroff said: “At present over 90 building projects are stuck at Dronagiri due to lack of OC. However, builders' lobby is in talks with the central and state governments to resolve the issue at the earliest.”

news.title: SC directs sale of 22 properties of Holy Faith Builders as payout for flat owners
news.para: The H2O Holy Faith was one among the four high-end apartment complexes in Maradu which was demolished in January 2020 for violation of coastal regulation zone (CRZ) rules. The SC order was in the wake of the report that the builder failed to pay the balance amount as directed by the court in 2019.

news.title: Chandigarh: Four more cheating FIRs filed against Gupta builders
news.para: As many as 13 FIRs have been registered against the directors of the GBP in the city. The accused are absconding. On Thursday, UT police had registered two cheating FIRs against the group.

news.title: Mhada set to receive 5,000 units from Nashik builders
news.para: State housing minister Jitendra Awhad had also tweeted, alleging financial irregularities worth Rs700 crore in the NMC for not transferring such flats to Mhada.

news.title: Credai Nagpur holds meet on online approval system
news.para: This OBPMS brings in a system of faceless approval of building plans, making the process faster. As there are certain technical bottlenecks in the system, some local authorities have sought extension in its implementation for the time being.

news.title: Rs 100 crore land scam in Kukatpally: Forum for Good Governance
news.para: FGG secretary M Padmanabha Reddy said Hyderabad Industries employees mutually aided co-operative society had taken control of 45 acres of land, including 12 open spaces spread over five acres, meant for community purposes.

news.title: Mindtree pre-leases 6 lakh sq ft office space in L&T's upcoming IT Park in Chennai
news.para: The over 10-year lease deal is for L&T Innovation Campus, a mixed-use development sprawling over 40 acres, two people aware of the deal said.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board delinks violations in buildings from flat transfers
news.para: Hundreds of pending applications because of the issue of building violations will now be finalised in the next few weeks and allottees/transferees will come forward with better confidence of getting the transfer/mutation permissions without inspections, Garg said.
